Genetic analysis of 103 SARS-CoV-2 genomes has identified two major strains designated as L-type and S-type.
5 S-type SARS-CoV-2 is the ancestral and less aggressive strain of the virus, with approximately 30% prevalence. L-type SARS-Cov-2 is thought to have evolved from the S-type virus and is both more aggressive and more prevalent (70%).
